Fodor and the six hundred Hungarians
As reported by the Minister of Environment and Hydrology Gábor Fodor, expert-level meetings will be completed on Tuesday and Wednesday after the official inauguration will continue minister-level negotiations on the international climate regime after 2012.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries around the world deliberate on the Bali Road Sheet that has the following efforts to reduce the emissions, established in the Kyoto Protocol, current until 2012.
Today, lively discussions are held on the particular issue between developing countries and industrialized countries.
The United States has already indicated that it does not want to negotiate accurate figures, although it tends to reach the agreement that compared to the 1990 situation, by 2020 the emissions of greenhouse gases responsible for the effect decreases by 25 to 40 percent.
Another major issue of the conference is that if industrialized countries, in addition to reducing emissions, are or are not willing to provide material and technological assistance to countries that need it.
Furthermore, an agreement was reached on aid to developing countries.
The support fund, provided for in the Kyoto Protocol, will be led by a management board of 16 members, probably within the UN Global Environment Fund (GEF) - writes the "Piac is Profit".
Six percent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, the Minister of Environment and Hydrology Gábor Fodor supports EU efforts to preserve its leading role in global climate protection and promote the signing of the new international agreement until 2009.
The minister stated that the EU is committed to reducing its gas emissions by 20 per cent until 2020, with respect to the 1990 level, responsible for the greenhouse effect, regardless of whether or not the “agreement after 2012” will be signed and is willing to commit to decrease even by 30 per cent if the other major developed regions of the world and developing countries are also willing to take their responsibilities.
Gábor Fodor pointed out that the countries signed by the 1997 Kyoto Protocol committed to decline by 5.2 percent, within that 15 EU member states committed to complying with 8% decline.
Hungary’s commitment is to decrease greenhouse gas emissions by 6 percent over the period between 1985 and 87, which our country will fulfill, says the press release of the Ministry of Environment.
It is a lot that is at stake in Bali, since within two years it will have to sign the long-term international climate policy agreement, because if not, it is sure that its entry into force would be delayed to after 2012. In this case the Nobel Climate Reduction Compliances, assigned in the Kyoto Protocol, would not be immediately followed by a new international system of emission reduction, which the UNCC was added in its most recently.
Thus, the reduction in emissions would suffer a delay and could not prevent an increase of more than 2°C in Earth’s average temperature, which, according to scientists, would have unmeasurable and irreversible consequences.
The British Army Recruits on YouTube
The British army units in a video distributor publish recordings on filmed actions in Iraq and Afghanistan to popularize themselves.
First the British Air Force (RAD) took advantage of YouTube’s services: special units displaced in Afghanistan since March 2006 are loading videos about their actions against the Taliban.
These recordings made with mini cameras mounted on the helmets are controlled in Kandahar’s overall operations body, then sent to London to be loaded to the Internet.
The political message is inevitable.
There are already 139 recordings from the soldiers of the air force that have been loaded on the Internet in this way and their "channel" has already been seen by more than 75,000 people.
The British Ministry of Defense registered in spring 2007 under the name of "defense headquarters" and publishes videos of both actions carried out in Iraq and Afghanistan, while both the Ministry of the British Nations Community (Commonwealth Office) and multinational forces in Iraq have their own YouTube channel.
Operation in Afghanistan
Originally the air force had loaded the videos with recruitment objectives, but in the opinion of the Ministry of Defense also serve to present to the public the true goal of the British army’s presence abroad.
This type of propaganda costs almost nothing compared to conventional recruitment television spots - told BBC defense expert Gordon Mackenzie - instead, they inevitably have some political message, since in a specific way they justify the reason of being the military actions decided by the government.
Americans prepared a video game
The army is also concerned that, in addition to the repeatedly edited and censored recordings, in the distributor also appear amateur videos, for example about the death of soldiers: in the "official" propaganda movies, a little hypocrites, officers talk to the maximum of losses, however presenting the bloody part of the fights.
Furthermore, the battlefields of Iraq and Afghanistan have been loaded to the Internet already numerous videos recorded in real operations, but the British army is only recently taking advantage of this opportunity.
Americans use a slightly different form for recruiting with free downloadable shooting video games, called America's Army, where in the middle of a more or less real situation the player can get directly instead of the soldiers.
