Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk of the Hungarian Guard increases
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the Hungarian Guard’s activity, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
The company’s “Risk Warning” writes: “In relation to the Hungarian Guard’s activity, the highest political risk constitutes the fact that “with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Gyptic and non-Gyptic population of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic confrontations can occur.”
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard’s political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this character, the representative of the research institute added.
They claimed that all this is due to one of the main mistakes of Hungarian political life protagonists: “The protagonists of public life gave him the public debate of the Citizen problem to representatives of the radical and extremist political groupings, who were able to found their political strategy on the existing differences between Citizens and Hungarians.”
This aggravates the problem, impossibilizes normal dialogue, strengthens extremists, and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts.
In addition to that, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, “deteriorated significantly the image of Hungary abroad, especially regarding the stability and democratic development of the country.”
They remind us that since the autumn of 2006, it has received increasingly advertising and boosting the reorganization of the radical and extreme-right Hungary groups and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been established in the country that are self-defined as "national self-defense associations".
“The common feature of these groups is that they are self-defined as civil organizations, while openly proclaim the training of their members for defense – even armed – (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), referring to the inability of the police, of the army, that is, of the state.”
They asserted that all this happens in accordance with the method that attempts to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the dissatisfaction of society with politics and with political parties.
Because highlighting the civilian and the form of association in the case of these associations does not only serve to avoid legal issues of legal enrollment, but is at the same time also a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the Hungarian Guard’s activity is also a risk factor from the point of view of neighborhood relationships.
“In recent months, many neighbouring states referred to the Hungarian Guard as a potential danger, while the ultra-national political figures of certain neighbouring countries want to justify their own anti-Hungarian policy with the creation of the Hungarian Guard.
All this influences the political stability of the region.”
