United Internet already on the day before made nearly 10 percent of the telecommunication company Drillisch participate.
Drillisch in the extent of capital enlargement placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, companies began negotiations on marketing cooperations of DSL-products.
"We strengthen our collaboration," United Internet spokesman explained.
The two companies founded a joint MSP company, to acquire the Freenet competitor.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at the beginning, the two companies want to be happy with the share of ten percent on Freenet and do not make use of their right, i.e., they make 18.49 percent on Freenet.
That meant that both companies kept all the options, especially participation in Freenet’s anonymous society.
The negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German market of Telecom.
At the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now, the holding of United Internet and Drillisch had directly 6.01 percent of Freenet stake.
Then they had agreed that Drilllich is going to achieve the other four percent.
